Police in Glasgow have seized heroin with a street value of &pound;210,000 during a drugs raid.
Officers recovered the Class A drugs while executing a warrant at a property in Foresthall Crescent.
Two men, aged 22 and 44, and two women, aged 19 and 45, arrested in connection with the raid are expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Monday.
Police said the &quot;significant recovery&quot; underlined their determination to crack down on drug-related crime.
